SIMPLE: delate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Delate
<hw>De*late"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Delated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Delating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>delatus</ets>, used as
p. p. of <ets>deferre</ets>. See <er>Tolerate</er>, and cf. 3d
<er>Defer</er>, <er>Delay</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <mark>[Obs. or
Archaic]</mark> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To carry; to convey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Try exactly the time wherein sound is <qex>delated</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To carry abroad; to spread; to make
public.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When the crime is <qex>delated</qex> or notorious.</q>
<rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To carry or bring against, as a charge; to inform
against; to accuse; to denounce.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As men were <qex>delated</qex>, they were marked down for such a
fine.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Burnet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To carry on; to conduct.</def>
<rj><au>Warner.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Delate</ent>⟦br⟧

